Cook, I thought it over and on the chance that I over-reacted to the 1st Cav issue, I apologize. I do not feel that anyone who did their part incountry has to apologize for doing their job and for surviving the shit, whether a desk jockey in Saigon to those of us who were in the field.<br><br>
I am also very protective of those that were WIA and KIA in the course of doing what was asked of them. Especially those that I was involved with.<br><br>
So, if it looks like I was looking for a fight, I wasn't. What I said about the Corps and the members of the same, is true. You, I'm sure inadvertantly, found a couple of my buttons.<br><br>
BC - you sorry mudder-trucker old man! It's about time you got off your ass and said something. But did it have to be a smartass remark...........
